(303, 0, 'rss_3d34718d2bd53aa33452af979e0b1d1f', 'O:9:"MagpieRSS":17:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:10:{i:0;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:35:"Dear hoster : We need more memory !";s:4:"link";s:73:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/";s:8:"comments";s:82:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sun, 14 Jun 2009 18:24:50 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:31:"PluginsWordpressmemory_limitphp";s:4:"guid";s:73:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/";s:11:"description";s:297:"A lot of people update to WordPress 2.8 and get the message :\r\nAllowed memory size of 33554433 bytes exhausted\r\nSo, with WP2.8 we reached now the limit of many hosters (32MB), who is the bad boy ? Can we increase the limit ? I faced a similar problem here with my homepage and wrote a simple [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:781:"<p>A lot of people update to WordPress 2.8 and get the message :</p>\n<blockquote><p>Allowed memory size of 33554433 bytes exhausted</p></blockquote>\n<p>So, with WP2.8 we reached now the limit of many hosters (32MB), who is the bad boy ? Can we increase the limit ? I faced a similar problem here with my homepage and wrote a simple plugin for the WordPress dashboard which shows up the limit and current usage. Just for the notes, a Wordpress 2.3 + NextGEN Gallery and 10 other plugins require <strong>16.32 Mbyte</strong> memory.</p>\n<p>Ok, what is the limit for a fresh <strong>WordPress 2.8</strong> installation under PHP 4 and PHP 5 ?</p>\n<p> <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/#more-326" class="more-link">(more&#8230;)</a></p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:78:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:297:"A lot of people update to WordPress 2.8 and get the message :\r\nAllowed memory size of 33554433 bytes exhausted\r\nSo, with WP2.8 we reached now the limit of many hosters (32MB), who is the bad boy ? Can we increase the limit ? I faced a similar problem here with my homepage and wrote a simple [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:781:"<p>A lot of people update to WordPress 2.8 and get the message :</p>\n<blockquote><p>Allowed memory size of 33554433 bytes exhausted</p></blockquote>\n<p>So, with WP2.8 we reached now the limit of many hosters (32MB), who is the bad boy ? Can we increase the limit ? I faced a similar problem here with my homepage and wrote a simple plugin for the WordPress dashboard which shows up the limit and current usage. Just for the notes, a Wordpress 2.3 + NextGEN Gallery and 10 other plugins require <strong>16.32 Mbyte</strong> memory.</p>\n<p>Ok, what is the limit for a fresh <strong>WordPress 2.8</strong> installation under PHP 4 and PHP 5 ?</p>\n<p> <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/14/dear-hoster-we-need-more-memory/#more-326" class="more-link">(more&#8230;)</a></p>\n";}i:1;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:28:"Bugfix release Version 1.3.2";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/10/bugfix-release-version-132/";s:8:"comments";s:77:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/10/bugfix-release-version-132/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 10 Jun 2009 18:00:00 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:38:"NextGEN GallerybugfixesNextGEN-Gallery";s:4:"guid";s:68:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/10/bugfix-release-version-132/";s:11:"description";s:299:"I must apologize the bug release of Version 1.3.x, there are more problems inside as I expected. I will do my best to sort out all issues, please be so kind and open a new thread at the forums when you have still problems with the new version.\r\n\r\nIn this minutes I uploaded Version 1.3.2, if [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:642:"<p>I must apologize the bug release of Version 1.3.x, there are more problems inside as I expected. I will do my best to sort out all issues, please be so kind and open a new thread at the forums when you have still problems with the new version.</p>\n<p>In this minutes I uploaded Version 1.3.2, if you want to use the automatic upgrade it can takes a couple of hours until your WordPress installation recognize the new update.</p>\n<p>Thanks for all the help at the forums !</p>\n<p class="download"><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/nextgen-gallery/">Download NextGEN Gallery Version 1.3.3 </a><br />\nRelease @ wordpress.org</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:73:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/10/bugfix-release-version-132/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:299:"I must apologize the bug release of Version 1.3.x, there are more problems inside as I expected. I will do my best to sort out all issues, please be so kind and open a new thread at the forums when you have still problems with the new version.\r\n\r\nIn this minutes I uploaded Version 1.3.2, if [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:642:"<p>I must apologize the bug release of Version 1.3.x, there are more problems inside as I expected. I will do my best to sort out all issues, please be so kind and open a new thread at the forums when you have still problems with the new version.</p>\n<p>In this minutes I uploaded Version 1.3.2, if you want to use the automatic upgrade it can takes a couple of hours until your WordPress installation recognize the new update.</p>\n<p>Thanks for all the help at the forums !</p>\n<p class="download"><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/nextgen-gallery/">Download NextGEN Gallery Version 1.3.3 </a><br />\nRelease @ wordpress.org</p>\n";}i:2;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:42:"Subalbum - NextGEN Gallery V1.3.0 released";s:4:"link";s:80:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/07/subalbum-nextgen-gallery-v130-released/";s:8:"comments";s:89:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/07/subalbum-nextgen-gallery-v130-released/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sun, 07 Jun 2009 12:03:01 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:52:"NextGEN GalleryWordpressNextGEN-Gallerywordpress 2.8";s:4:"guid";s:80:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/07/subalbum-nextgen-gallery-v130-released/";s:11:"description";s:357:"As you can read from the WordPress blog, theversion2.8 should be released on June, 10th. So Ispeedup the release of NGG , I hope there are no more major bugs inside. What is new in this version ?\r\n\r\nThere are two,three things I would highlight :\r\n\r\n1. Subalbum support\r\n\r\nAsoftenrequested, I extend thealbumsystem in the way that you [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2757:"<p>As you can read from the WordPress blog, theversion2.8 should be released on <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2009/06/summary-of-wordpress-dev-irc-meetup-for-20090603/">June, 10th</a>. So Ispeedup the release of NGG , I hope there are no more major bugs inside. <em>What is new in this version ?</em></p>\n<p>There are two,three things I would highlight :</p>\n<p><strong>1. Subalbum support</strong></p>\n<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/subalbum.png" rel="lightbox" title="Subalbum"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/subalbum.thumbnail.png" alt="Subalbum" align="left" /></a>Asoftenrequested, I extend thealbumsystem in the way that you can add aalbuminside another album. Therefore you can add now on the album page for each album a description text and a preview image. As limitation you are not longer able to add more that one album to a post/page.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Search for images</strong></p>\n<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/search.png" rel="lightbox" title="Search"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/search.thumbnail.png" alt="Search" align="left" /></a>In the gallery tab you are now able tosearchfor images. I know that many people requested as well asearchin thefront-end,buthere I need a bit more time. It&#8217;s still on my task list&#8230;</p>\n<p><strong>3. AJAX navigation for gallery and imagebrowser</strong><br />\nThanks to the contribution from Anty we have now a Ajaxnavigation. See a demo here : <a href="http://nextgen.boelinger.com/image-browser/">Imagebrowser</a> or <a href="http://nextgen.boelinger.com/gallery-page/">gallery</a>. It&#8217;s limited to the inbuilt Shutter reloaded effect, so if you use any other javascript image effect it&#8217;s requires a modification of the AJAX script code. You can request help at the forums.</p>\n<p>Here is the full changelog :</p>\n<p>- NEW : Subalbum support<br />\n- NEW : Search for images in the admin tab<br />\n- NEW : Add new gallery also in manage tab<br />\n- NEW : AJAX support for Imagebrowser and gallery navigation (THX to Anty)<br />\n- NEW : Added zip upload via URL (THX to Juan Jose Galvez)<br />\n- Added : jQuery Multiple File Upload Plugin v1.44<br />\n- Added : SWFUpload V2.2.0<br />\n- Changed : Remove extension for Alttext during first import<br />\n- Changed : Meta tag added via wp_head hook (THX to Viper)<br />\n- Bugfix : Correct various PHP notice messages<br />\n- Bugfix : Typo fix in custom fields for ngg_gal_ImageBrowser<br />\n- Bugfix : Avoid upload of images in gallery without correct capability</p>\n<p>As always please request help via the wordpress.org forums, no help in the comment section.</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:85:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/07/subalbum-nextgen-gallery-v130-released/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:357:"As you can read from the WordPress blog, theversion2.8 should be released on June, 10th. So Ispeedup the release of NGG , I hope there are no more major bugs inside. What is new in this version ?\r\n\r\nThere are two,three things I would highlight :\r\n\r\n1. Subalbum support\r\n\r\nAsoftenrequested, I extend thealbumsystem in the way that you [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:2757:"<p>As you can read from the WordPress blog, theversion2.8 should be released on <a href="http://wordpress.org/development/2009/06/summary-of-wordpress-dev-irc-meetup-for-20090603/">June, 10th</a>. So Ispeedup the release of NGG , I hope there are no more major bugs inside. <em>What is new in this version ?</em></p>\n<p>There are two,three things I would highlight :</p>\n<p><strong>1. Subalbum support</strong></p>\n<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/subalbum.png" rel="lightbox" title="Subalbum"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/subalbum.thumbnail.png" alt="Subalbum" align="left" /></a>Asoftenrequested, I extend thealbumsystem in the way that you can add aalbuminside another album. Therefore you can add now on the album page for each album a description text and a preview image. As limitation you are not longer able to add more that one album to a post/page.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Search for images</strong></p>\n<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/search.png" rel="lightbox" title="Search"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/search.thumbnail.png" alt="Search" align="left" /></a>In the gallery tab you are now able tosearchfor images. I know that many people requested as well asearchin thefront-end,buthere I need a bit more time. It&#8217;s still on my task list&#8230;</p>\n<p><strong>3. AJAX navigation for gallery and imagebrowser</strong><br />\nThanks to the contribution from Anty we have now a Ajaxnavigation. See a demo here : <a href="http://nextgen.boelinger.com/image-browser/">Imagebrowser</a> or <a href="http://nextgen.boelinger.com/gallery-page/">gallery</a>. It&#8217;s limited to the inbuilt Shutter reloaded effect, so if you use any other javascript image effect it&#8217;s requires a modification of the AJAX script code. You can request help at the forums.</p>\n<p>Here is the full changelog :</p>\n<p>- NEW : Subalbum support<br />\n- NEW : Search for images in the admin tab<br />\n- NEW : Add new gallery also in manage tab<br />\n- NEW : AJAX support for Imagebrowser and gallery navigation (THX to Anty)<br />\n- NEW : Added zip upload via URL (THX to Juan Jose Galvez)<br />\n- Added : jQuery Multiple File Upload Plugin v1.44<br />\n- Added : SWFUpload V2.2.0<br />\n- Changed : Remove extension for Alttext during first import<br />\n- Changed : Meta tag added via wp_head hook (THX to Viper)<br />\n- Bugfix : Correct various PHP notice messages<br />\n- Bugfix : Typo fix in custom fields for ngg_gal_ImageBrowser<br />\n- Bugfix : Avoid upload of images in gallery without correct capability</p>\n<p>As always please request help via the wordpress.org forums, no help in the comment section.</p>\n";}i:3;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:29:"NextGEN Gallery v1.3.0 Beta 1";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/03/nextgen-gallery-v130-beta-1/";s:8:"comments";s:78:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/03/nextgen-gallery-v130-beta-1/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 03 Jun 2009 20:53:14 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:47:"NextGEN GallerybetaNextGEN-Gallerywordpress 2.8";s:4:"guid";s:69:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/03/nextgen-gallery-v130-beta-1/";s:11:"description";s:294:"WordPress 2.8 is on the way and I fixed therefore a couple of compat issues. You can help me now with testing the next release step V1.3.0. It should work as well under WordPress 2.7, but the design in the album page is already fitted to the UI of WordPress 2.8.\r\n\r\nYou mainly ask what is [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:521:"<p>WordPress 2.8 is on the way and I fixed therefore a couple of compat issues. You can help me now with testing the next release step V1.3.0. It should work as well under WordPress 2.7, but the design in the album page is already fitted to the UI of WordPress 2.8.</p>\n<p><em>You mainly ask what is new ?</em> I will write some more information at release date, you can have a first look at the change log <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wordpress-plugins/nextgen-gallery/changelog/">here</a>. Happy testing.</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:74:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/06/03/nextgen-gallery-v130-beta-1/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:294:"WordPress 2.8 is on the way and I fixed therefore a couple of compat issues. You can help me now with testing the next release step V1.3.0. It should work as well under WordPress 2.7, but the design in the album page is already fitted to the UI of WordPress 2.8.\r\n\r\nYou mainly ask what is [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:521:"<p>WordPress 2.8 is on the way and I fixed therefore a couple of compat issues. You can help me now with testing the next release step V1.3.0. It should work as well under WordPress 2.7, but the design in the album page is already fitted to the UI of WordPress 2.8.</p>\n<p><em>You mainly ask what is new ?</em> I will write some more information at release date, you can have a first look at the change log <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wordpress-plugins/nextgen-gallery/changelog/">here</a>. Happy testing.</p>\n";}i:4;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:5:"Snipi";s:4:"link";s:47:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/25/snipi/";s:8:"comments";s:56:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/25/snipi/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 25 May 2009 19:38:11 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:46:"CommonNextGEN GalleryNextGEN-Gallerysnipivideo";s:4:"guid";s:47:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/25/snipi/";s:11:"description";s:270:"A new tools for Firefox called Snipi is now available. You can drag and drop products, photos and videos from virtually anywhere and organize, share and compare. They also write a new pluginfor WordPress. See it here in action :\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAny thoughts about such a tool ?";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:885:"<p>A new tools for Firefox called <a href="http://www.snipi.com/">Snipi</a> is now available. You can drag and drop products, photos and videos from virtually anywhere and organize, share and compare. They also write a new <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/snipi-for-wordpress-media-library-and-nextgen-gallery/">plugin</a>for WordPress. See it here in action :</p>\n<p><object width="480" height="385">\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/73iNmJ1k-2c&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1&#038;rel=0"></param>\n<param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param>\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/73iNmJ1k-2c&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1&#038;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="480" height="385"></embed></object></p>\n<p>Any thoughts about such a tool ?</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:52:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/25/snipi/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:270:"A new tools for Firefox called Snipi is now available. You can drag and drop products, photos and videos from virtually anywhere and organize, share and compare. They also write a new pluginfor WordPress. See it here in action :\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAny thoughts about such a tool ?";s:12:"atom_content";s:885:"<p>A new tools for Firefox called <a href="http://www.snipi.com/">Snipi</a> is now available. You can drag and drop products, photos and videos from virtually anywhere and organize, share and compare. They also write a new <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/snipi-for-wordpress-media-library-and-nextgen-gallery/">plugin</a>for WordPress. See it here in action :</p>\n<p><object width="480" height="385">\n<param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/73iNmJ1k-2c&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1&#038;rel=0"></param>\n<param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param>\n<param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/73iNmJ1k-2c&#038;hl=en&#038;fs=1&#038;rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="480" height="385"></embed></object></p>\n<p>Any thoughts about such a tool ?</p>\n";}i:5;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:19:"Javascript overload";s:4:"link";s:61:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/18/javascript-overload/";s:8:"comments";s:70:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/18/javascript-overload/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 18 May 2009 18:40:17 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:21:"AllerleiframeworkQNAP";s:4:"guid";s:61:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/18/javascript-overload/";s:11:"description";s:309:"I setup this weekend my new NAS (QNAP TS-219). It''s very fast and I finished the installation within 2 hours. Then I start to play with the features &#38; functions. The admin backend is really nice and easy to understand, but I recognize that it require a lot of loading time... Switched on firebug and [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:782:"<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/qnap_backend.png" rel="lightbox" title="QNAP Backend"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/qnap_backend.thumbnail.png" alt="QNAP Backend" align="left" /></a>I setup this weekend my new NAS (QNAP TS-219). It&#8217;s very fast and I finished the installation within 2 hours. Then I start to play with the features &amp; functions. The admin backend is really nice and easy to understand, but I recognize that it require a lot of loading time&#8230; Switched on firebug and get shocked, I never have seen so much javascript libraries loaded at the same time&#8230; Overall 2 MB (!) and nearly all existing Javascript frameworks. Hey QNAP Guys , a nice backend is cool, but try a smaller footprint.</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:66:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/18/javascript-overload/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:309:"I setup this weekend my new NAS (QNAP TS-219). It''s very fast and I finished the installation within 2 hours. Then I start to play with the features &#38; functions. The admin backend is really nice and easy to understand, but I recognize that it require a lot of loading time... Switched on firebug and [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:782:"<p><a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/qnap_backend.png" rel="lightbox" title="QNAP Backend"><img src="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-content/uploads/qnap_backend.thumbnail.png" alt="QNAP Backend" align="left" /></a>I setup this weekend my new NAS (QNAP TS-219). It&#8217;s very fast and I finished the installation within 2 hours. Then I start to play with the features &amp; functions. The admin backend is really nice and easy to understand, but I recognize that it require a lot of loading time&#8230; Switched on firebug and get shocked, I never have seen so much javascript libraries loaded at the same time&#8230; Overall 2 MB (!) and nearly all existing Javascript frameworks. Hey QNAP Guys , a nice backend is cool, but try a smaller footprint.</p>\n";}i:6;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:23:"NextGEN for your Header";s:4:"link";s:65:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/05/nextgen-for-your-header/";s:8:"comments";s:74:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/05/nextgen-for-your-header/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 05 May 2009 19:48:23 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:30:"NextGEN GalleryNextGEN-Gallery";s:4:"guid";s:65:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/05/nextgen-for-your-header/";s:11:"description";s:317:"There is a very good tutorial how to integrate the slideshow into your header at berchman.com.\r\n\r\nA great example is the page designed by Angela Bowman : http://gotravelghana.com/\r\n\r\nBy the way :NGG 1.3.0 is on the road, I already fixed all issues with the upcoming WP.2.8 and added a search feature for the backend";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:480:"<p>There is a very good tutorial how to integrate the slideshow into your header at <a href="http://www.berchman.com/thesis-tutorial-dynamic-image-header-with-transparent-logo/">berchman.com</a>.</p>\n<p>A great example is the page designed by Angela Bowman : <a href="http://gotravelghana.com/">http://gotravelghana.com/</a></p>\n<p><em>By the way :</em>NGG 1.3.0 is on the road, I already fixed all issues with the upcoming WP.2.8 and added a search feature for the backend</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:70:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/05/05/nextgen-for-your-header/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:317:"There is a very good tutorial how to integrate the slideshow into your header at berchman.com.\r\n\r\nA great example is the page designed by Angela Bowman : http://gotravelghana.com/\r\n\r\nBy the way :NGG 1.3.0 is on the road, I already fixed all issues with the upcoming WP.2.8 and added a search feature for the backend";s:12:"atom_content";s:480:"<p>There is a very good tutorial how to integrate the slideshow into your header at <a href="http://www.berchman.com/thesis-tutorial-dynamic-image-header-with-transparent-logo/">berchman.com</a>.</p>\n<p>A great example is the page designed by Angela Bowman : <a href="http://gotravelghana.com/">http://gotravelghana.com/</a></p>\n<p><em>By the way :</em>NGG 1.3.0 is on the road, I already fixed all issues with the upcoming WP.2.8 and added a search feature for the backend</p>\n";}i:7;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:27:"NextGEN Gallery @ Ohloh.net";s:4:"link";s:66:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/";s:8:"comments";s:75:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Fri, 17 Apr 2009 08:01:55 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:30:"NextGEN GalleryNextGEN-Gallery";s:4:"guid";s:66:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/";s:11:"description";s:104:"If you add your WordPress Plugin to Ohloh.net , you receive a couple of interesting statistics :\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:348:"<p>If you add your WordPress Plugin to Ohloh.net , you receive a couple of interesting statistics :</p>\n<p><script src="http://www.ohloh.net/p/21827/widgets/project_basic_stats.js" type="text/javascript"></script></p>\n<p> <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/#more-316" class="more-link">(more&#8230;)</a></p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:71:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:104:"If you add your WordPress Plugin to Ohloh.net , you receive a couple of interesting statistics :\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n";s:12:"atom_content";s:348:"<p>If you add your WordPress Plugin to Ohloh.net , you receive a couple of interesting statistics :</p>\n<p><script src="http://www.ohloh.net/p/21827/widgets/project_basic_stats.js" type="text/javascript"></script></p>\n<p> <a href="http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/17/nextgen-gallery-ohlohnet/#more-316" class="more-link">(more&#8230;)</a></p>\n";}i:8;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:26:"Looking for a NAS solution";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/01/looking-for-a-nas-solution/";s:8:"comments";s:77:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/01/looking-for-a-nas-solution/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 01 Apr 2009 09:09:01 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:42:"NextGEN GalleryNASNextGEN-Gallerysearching";s:4:"guid";s:68:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/01/looking-for-a-nas-solution/";s:11:"description";s:344:"During the last days I''m crawling the web to findthe bestNAS for my home office. I would like to have a web server possibility, so that I can implement WordPress with NextGEN Gallery and wordTube. Funny thing,QNAP already tested and documented my plugin : Look this application note. It''s better than my own documentation :-)\r\n\r\nThe [...]";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:930:"<p>During the last days I&#8217;m crawling the web to findthe bestNAS for my home office. I would like to have a web server possibility, so that I can implement WordPress with NextGEN Gallery and wordTube. Funny thing,QNAP already tested and documented my plugin : <a href="http://www.qnap.com/pro_application.asp?ap_id=97">Look this application note</a>. It&#8217;s better than my own documentation <img src=''http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>The brand new <a href="http://www.qnap.com/pro_detail_feature.asp?p_id=112">QNAP TS-119</a>is currently my favorite NAS, alternative the <a href="http://www.synology.com/enu/products/DS107+/index.php">Synology DS107+</a>seems to be working with WordPress. Any experience from your side with QNAP or Synology ? Which one can your recommend ? Have you experience with WordPress and a other NAS ?</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:73:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/04/01/looking-for-a-nas-solution/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:344:"During the last days I''m crawling the web to findthe bestNAS for my home office. I would like to have a web server possibility, so that I can implement WordPress with NextGEN Gallery and wordTube. Funny thing,QNAP already tested and documented my plugin : Look this application note. It''s better than my own documentation :-)\r\n\r\nThe [...]";s:12:"atom_content";s:930:"<p>During the last days I&#8217;m crawling the web to findthe bestNAS for my home office. I would like to have a web server possibility, so that I can implement WordPress with NextGEN Gallery and wordTube. Funny thing,QNAP already tested and documented my plugin : <a href="http://www.qnap.com/pro_application.asp?ap_id=97">Look this application note</a>. It&#8217;s better than my own documentation <img src=''http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>The brand new <a href="http://www.qnap.com/pro_detail_feature.asp?p_id=112">QNAP TS-119</a>is currently my favorite NAS, alternative the <a href="http://www.synology.com/enu/products/DS107+/index.php">Synology DS107+</a>seems to be working with WordPress. Any experience from your side with QNAP or Synology ? Which one can your recommend ? Have you experience with WordPress and a other NAS ?</p>\n";}i:9;a:12:{s:5:"title";s:37:"Vote for your favorite gallery plugin";s:4:"link";s:79:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/03/28/vote-for-your-favorite-gallery-plugin/";s:8:"comments";s:88:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/03/28/vote-for-your-favorite-gallery-plugin/#comments";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Sat, 28 Mar 2009 13:38:30 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"alex.rabe";}s:8:"category";s:52:"NextGEN GallerybrainstromingideasNextGEN-GalleryVote";s:4:"guid";s:79:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/03/28/vote-for-your-favorite-gallery-plugin/";s:11:"description";s:274:"I''m currently sorting out what could be the next feature for NGG, in the meantime you can vote your favorite gallery plugin at BlogOh!Blog . I''m also interesting in the pro''s and con''s about your experience with NGG. Let me know your opinion in the comment section. Thanks !";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:373:"<p>I&#8217;m currently sorting out what could be the next feature for NGG, in the meantime you can vote your favorite gallery plugin at <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/wordpress-gallery-plugins/">BlogOh!Blog</a> . I&#8217;m also interesting in the pro&#8217;s and con&#8217;s about your experience with NGG. Let me know your opinion in the comment section. Thanks !</p>\n";}s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:84:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com/2009/03/28/vote-for-your-favorite-gallery-plugin/feed/";}s:7:"summary";s:274:"I''m currently sorting out what could be the next feature for NGG, in the meantime you can vote your favorite gallery plugin at BlogOh!Blog . I''m also interesting in the pro''s and con''s about your experience with NGG. Let me know your opinion in the comment section. Thanks !";s:12:"atom_content";s:373:"<p>I&#8217;m currently sorting out what could be the next feature for NGG, in the meantime you can vote your favorite gallery plugin at <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/wordpress-gallery-plugins/">BlogOh!Blog</a> . I&#8217;m also interesting in the pro&#8217;s and con&#8217;s about your experience with NGG. Let me know your opinion in the comment section. Thanks !</p>\n";}}s:7:"channel";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:9:"alex.rabe";s:4:"link";s:29:"http://alexrabe.boelinger.com";s:11:"description";s:32:"ALEX RABE | learning by doing...";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 15 Jun 2009 14:02:34 +0000";s:9:"generator";s:29:"http://wordpress.org/?v=2.3.3";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:7:"tagline";s:32:"ALEX RABE | learning by doing...";}s:9:"textinput";a:0:{}s:5:"image";a:0:{}s:9:"feed_type";s:3:"RSS";s:12:"feed_version";s:3:"2.0";s:5:"stack";a:0:{}s:9:"inchannel";b:0;s:6:"initem";b:0;s:9:"incontent";b:0;s:11:"intextinput";b:0;s:7:"inimage";b:0;s:13:"current_field";s:0:"";s:17:"current_namespace";b:0;s:19:"_CONTENT_CONSTRUCTS";a:6:{i:0;s:7:"content";i:1;s:7:"summary";i:2;s:4:"info";i:3;s:5:"title";i:4;s:7:"tagline";i:5;s:9:"copyright";}}', 'no'),
