(90, 1, '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra</li>\r\n	<li>1915 - Death of Mother</li>\r\n	<li>1917 - Death of Father</li>\r\n	<li>1918 - Leaves Home</li>\r\n	<li>1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)</li>\r\n	<li>1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru</li>\r\n	<li>1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage</li>\r\n	<li>1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.</li>\r\n	<li>1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.</li>\r\n	<li>1935 - Comes to Gagangad</li>\r\n	<li>1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode</li>\r\n	<li>1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.</li>\r\n	<li>1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile</li>\r\n	<li>1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad</li>\r\n	<li>1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.</li>\r\n	<li>1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.</li>\r\n	<li>1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur</li>\r\n	<li>1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function</li>\r\n	<li>1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island Ashrams were developed at Kalambe and \r\nPatan (at Satara) At Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\r\nDigit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\r\nKalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)</li>\r\n</ul>', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'history', '', '', '2009-06-09 08:56:16', '2009-06-09 08:56:16', '', 2, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/?page_id=90', 5, 'page', '', 0),
(91, 1, '2009-06-04 09:32:23', '2009-06-04 09:32:23', '', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-revision', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:32:23', '2009-06-04 09:32:23', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '    *  1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra\r\n    * 1915 - Death of Mother\r\n    * 1917 - Death of Father\r\n    * 1918 - Leaves Home\r\n    * 1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)\r\n    * 1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru\r\n    * 1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage\r\n    * 1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.\r\n    * 1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.\r\n    * 1935 - Comes to Gagangad\r\n    * 1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode\r\n    * 1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.\r\n    * 1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai\r\n    * 1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile\r\n    * 1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad\r\n    * 1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.\r\n    * 1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.\r\n    * 1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur\r\n    * 1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function\r\n    * 1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island\r\n                        Ashrams were developed at Kalambe and Patan (at Satara)\r\n                        At Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\r\n                        Digit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\r\n                        Kalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-revision-2', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '2009-06-04 09:33:01', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2009-06-04 09:33:28', '2009-06-04 09:33:28', '    *  1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra\r\n    * 1915 - Death of Mother\r\n    * 1917 - Death of Father\r\n    * 1918 - Leaves Home\r\n    * 1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)\r\n    * 1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru\r\n    * 1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage\r\n    * 1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.\r\n    * 1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.\r\n    * 1935 - Comes to Gagangad\r\n    * 1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode\r\n    * 1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.\r\n    * 1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai\r\n    * 1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile\r\n    * 1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad\r\n    * 1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.\r\n    * 1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.\r\n    * 1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur\r\n    * 1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function\r\n    * 1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island\r\n                             Ashrams were developed at Kalambe and Patan (at Satara)\r\n                             At Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\r\n                             Digit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\r\n                             Kalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)\r\n', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-revision-3', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:33:28', '2009-06-04 09:33:28', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Gagangad</li>\r\n	<li>Khopoli</li>\r\n	<li>Vesraf</li>\r\n	<li>Dajipur</li>\r\n	<li>Manori</li>\r\n	<li>Ambolgad Ashram : A very rocky sea side where Maharaj use to frequently visit for doing his sadhana, in the salty waters. He use to carry out different experiments with his body. He use to sit in these waters upto late night on full moon day and practise his mastery for having control over evil energy. He use to do this in the cremation grounds. In this way he use to help his devotees to overcome theirevil energies and bless them with positive energies (Blessings) in theirphysical and mental health.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'BRANCHES & CENTERS', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'branches-centers', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:39:29', '2009-06-04 09:39:29', '', 2, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/?page_id=94', 6, 'page', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2009-06-04 09:34:36', '2009-06-04 09:34:36', '', 'BRANCHES &', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-revision', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:34:36', '2009-06-04 09:34:36', '', 94, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/94-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(96, 1, '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '    *  Gagangad\r\n    * Khopoli\r\n    * Vesraf\r\n    * Dajipur\r\n    * Manori\r\n    * Ambolgad Ashram : A very rocky sea side where Maharaj use to frequently visit for doing his sadhana, in the salty waters. He use to carry out different experiments with his body. He use to sit in these waters upto late night on full moon day and practise his mastery for having control over evil energy. He use to do this in the cremation grounds. In this way he use to help his devotees to overcome theirevil energies and bless them with positive energies (Blessings) in theirphysical and mental health.\r\n      At times he use to apply layers of Sea Shell paste on his face, hands and feet and dry them in the hot scorching rays of the sun . Then he use to take a warm water bath boiled with medicinal hers after 6-8 hours of sitting in the sun.\r\n      Inspite of his while body getting sc scratchd and wounded at times with the strong rays on those hard rocks, he never deterred from the arduous of his penance.\r\n', 'BRANCHES & CENTERS', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-revision-2', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '2009-06-04 09:34:57', '', 94, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/94-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
