(175, 1, '2009-06-09 09:01:22', '2009-06-09 09:01:22', '<ul>\n	<li>1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra</li>\n	<li>1915 - Death of Mother</li>\n	<li>1917 - Death of Father</li>\n	<li>1918 - Leaves Home</li>\n	<li>1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)</li>\n	<li>1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru</li>\n	<li>1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage</li>\n	<li>1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.</li>\n	<li>1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.</li>\n	<li>1935 - Comes to Gagangad</li>\n	<li>1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode</li>\n	<li>1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.</li>\n	<li>1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai</li>\n	<li>1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile</li>\n	<li>1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad</li>\n	<li>1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.</li>\n	<li>1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.</li>\n	<li>1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur</li>\n	<li>1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function</li>\n	<li>1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island Ashrams were developed at Kalambe and\nPatan (at Satara) At Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\nDigit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\nKalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)</li>\n</ul>', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-autosave', '', '', '2009-06-09 09:01:22', '2009-06-09 09:01:22', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(176, 1, '2009-06-04 09:34:12', '2009-06-04 09:34:12', '    *  1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra\r\n    * 1915 - Death of Mother\r\n    * 1917 - Death of Father\r\n    * 1918 - Leaves Home\r\n    * 1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)\r\n    * 1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru\r\n    * 1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage\r\n    * 1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.\r\n    * 1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.\r\n    * 1935 - Comes to Gagangad\r\n    * 1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode\r\n    * 1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.\r\n    * 1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai\r\n    * 1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile\r\n    * 1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad\r\n    * 1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.\r\n    * 1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.\r\n    * 1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur\r\n    * 1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function\r\n    * 1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island\r\nAshrams were developed at Kalambe and Patan (at Satara)\r\n                             At Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\r\n                             Digit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\r\n                             Kalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)\r\n', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-revision-4', '', '', '2009-06-04 09:34:12', '2009-06-04 09:34:12', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2009-06-05 05:37:41', '2009-06-05 05:37:41', '<ul>\r\n	<li> 1911 - 1912 - Birth of Shripad in Patankar family at Mandure village in Maharashtra</li>\r\n	<li>1915 - Death of Mother</li>\r\n	<li>1917 - Death of Father</li>\r\n	<li>1918 - Leaves Home</li>\r\n	<li>1918 - Joins Shri Chitranand Maharaj Ashram, Chitrakoot (U. P.)</li>\r\n	<li>1920 - Goes to Himalayas along with his Guru</li>\r\n	<li>1931 - Returns to Zhansi after Himalayan Pilgrimage</li>\r\n	<li>1931-32 - Starts Pilgrimage to South India.</li>\r\n	<li>1932-33 - Comes to Dajipur Forest. Commences Penance in Dajipur.</li>\r\n	<li>1935 - Comes to Gagangad</li>\r\n	<li>1940 - Makes Gagangad his abode</li>\r\n	<li>1945-48 - Does Kaya-Kalpa Penance at Angale, Rajapur.</li>\r\n	<li>1949-50 - Does sadhana at Walkeshware in Mumbai</li>\r\n	<li>1950 - Maharaj becomes accessible to the people By doing his penance at Khopile</li>\r\n	<li>1960 - Chief Minister Balasaheb Desai gives news of Maharaj to his relations in Patan after visiting Gagangad</li>\r\n	<li>1962 - Celebration of Datta Jayanti Festival started.</li>\r\n	<li>1982 - Maharaj attends Nashik Kumbh Mela.</li>\r\n	<li>1987 - Penance at Ambolgad ashramn, near Rajapur</li>\r\n	<li>1990-1991 - Started visiting Damdodaran Ashram of Shri Gagnandji at Manori on Dussara function</li>\r\n	<li>1994-1995 - Created an Ashram at Manori island</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAshrams were developed at Kalambe and Patan (at Satara)\r\nAt Dhankal (Konianagar Satara), Phiba palace at Ratnagiri\r\nDigit Ashram (Kudal), Onee and Solgoan (Rajapur)\r\nKalavli and Saitavede Ashram (Gangangad)', 'HISTORY', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '90-revision-5', '', '', '2009-06-05 05:37:41', '2009-06-05 05:37:41', '', 90, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/90-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(178, 1, '2009-06-04 10:34:26', '2009-06-04 10:34:26', 'Khopoli is a city in the Indian state of Maharashtra, at the base of the Sahyadri mountains, near Karjat surrounded on all sides by hills.\r\n\r\nThe name khopoli was derived from the following two words. Khopi (means a hut) and awali (means a row) i.e many huts in a row.\r\n\r\nThere is a waterbody (generally called as shankar mandir talao). but the actual name of this waterbody is Kakan talao. The name to this water body was given because of a genuine reason. Once there was some queen and there was a drought in khopoli. So she had sold her diamond bangles (They were called Kakan in marathi, Kangan in Hindi) and hence the name Kakan talao. This talao is very deep. In the deep waters of the kakan talao lies an escape route of shivaji maharaj.\r\n\r\nThe (ghat section) the road which climbs through the mountains to lonavla is called the Bhor Ghat. This road was built by Dalhousie. It was the only way to many far off countries and the only way for transportation and so was of utmost importance.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OM Sadguru Pratishthan(Tembe Swami), P.P. Vasudevanand Saraswati Marg, New Township, Khopoli, Raigarh.</li>\r\n	<li>Bhagwan Parshuram Mandir and Agni Mandir - Papco Mills</li>\r\n	<li>Zenith waterfall and Ring waterfall</li>\r\n	<li>Sahyadri ranges during monsoon season</li>\r\n	<li>Shree Swami Samarth Math-Bhanvaj Road</li>\r\n	<li>Old Shiv temple and lake</li>\r\n	<li>Hazrat Gazibaba''s, Latif shah baba''s, Siddique shah baba and hazrat latif shah baba''s Dargahs.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'OTHER PLACES TO VISIT', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '150-revision-4', '', '', '2009-06-04 10:34:26', '2009-06-04 10:34:26', '', 150, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/150-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2009-06-05 06:46:14', '2009-06-05 06:46:14', 'Khopoli is a city in the Indian state of Maharashtra, at the base of the Sahyadri mountains, near Karjat surrounded on all sides by hills.\r\n\r\nThe name khopoli was derived from the following two words. Khopi (means a hut) and awali (means a row) i.e many huts in a row.\r\n\r\nThere is a waterbody (generally called as shankar mandir talao). but the actual name of this waterbody is Kakan talao. The name to this water body was given because of a genuine reason. Once there was some queen and there was a drought in khopoli. So she had sold her diamond bangles (They were called Kakan in marathi, Kangan in Hindi) and hence the name Kakan talao. This talao is very deep. In the deep waters of the kakan talao lies an escape route of shivaji maharaj.\r\n\r\nThe (ghat section) the road which climbs through the mountains to lonavla is called the Bhor Ghat. This road was built by Dalhousie. It was the only way to many far off countries and the only way for transportation and so was of utmost importance.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OM Sadguru Pratishthan(Tembe Swami), P.P. Vasudevanand Saraswati Marg, New Township, Khopoli, Raigarh.</li>\r\n	<li>Bhagwan Parshuram Mandir and Agni Mandir - Papco Mills</li>\r\n	<li>Zenith waterfall and Ring waterfall</li>\r\n	<li>Sahyadri ranges during monsoon season</li>\r\n	<li>Shree Swami Samarth Math-Bhanvaj Road</li>\r\n	<li>Old Shiv temple and lake</li>\r\n	<li>Hazrat Gazibaba''s, Latif shah baba''s, Siddique shah baba and hazrat latif shah baba''s Dargahs.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'OTHER PLACES TO VISIT', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '150-revision-5', '', '', '2009-06-05 06:46:14', '2009-06-05 06:46:14', '', 150, 'http://www.gagangiriv1.com/150-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
